  "text": "B16-F10 cells were used for melanin synthesis estimation, cells were counted using hemocytometer and plated in 90 mm culture dish at the density corresponding to 2 X 10 6 per 6 mL in culture plates. Further, the cells were incubated overnight under specified growth conditions and allowed for cell recovery and exponential growth. After incubation, the cells were treated with α-melanocyte-stimulating hormone (α-MSH) for a time point ranging from 4 to 24 hours for the stimulation of intracellular melanin synthesis. Further, the cells were incubated with α-MSH. After incubation, intracellular melanin was extracted in NaOH and the absorbance was recorded at 405 nm. The levels of melanin were extrapolated using standard curve obtained from purified melanin [CITATION_1] .",
